  "prompt": "What is the English word for the Tagalog word \u201ckinikilig\u201d?",
  "response": "The Tagalog word **\"kinikilig\"** refers to the feeling of excitement, giddiness, or butterflies in the stomach, often experienced when you\u2019re infatuated, in love, or thrilled by something romantic or exciting. The closest English equivalent would be **\"giddy\"** or **\"having butterflies\"**, or more specifically, **\"feeling thrilled\"** or **\"feeling excited\"** in a romantic or flustered way. \n\nFor example:\n- \"I\u2019m kinikilig because of him\" could be translated as \"I\u2019m giddy because of him\" or \"He gives me butterflies.\"",
